            <biogHist>
                <p>Neil MacPherson was born in 1781, son of John MacPherson, crofter, and Effy
                    MacPherson n√©e MacDonald. Far from being, as he appears in the Carmichael note,
                    an isolated pauper at Strome, the cottar settlement at the eastern end of
                    Lionacleit, Neil was simply there as an old, retired man living with his
                    youngest daughter, Joanna, and husband. He had been crofter at 21 Griminish
                    since holdings there were lotted off in 1818. He was from an important Benbecula
                    family, his brother being am Maor Iochdar and, according to strong local
                    tradition, these MacPhersons were MacMhuirichs who had come north from the
                    bardic holding at Stilligarry. He was married to Christina or Kirsty MacCormick
                    and he told Carmichael that he had 9 daughters, 51 grandchildren and 20 great
                    grandchildren.</p>
                <p>At the time of his death he was living in Liniclate with his youngest daughter
                    Joanna and her husband Angus MacCormick and the cause of his death was unknown. </p>
